cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CL, cs.LM, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a new modal logic and presents a sequent calculus for it. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the modality in type systems and program logics. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possibility as the paper deals with a logic that captures guarded recursion, which is relevant to natural language processing. 
- cs.LM (Logic in Mathematics) is a possibility as the paper uses the internal logic of the topos of trees to model the modality. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the decidability and complexity of the logic.
